53.8	Zoonosis	Zoonosis	A zoonosis ( ) or zoonose is any infectious disease that can be transmitted (in some instances, by a vector) from animals to humans or from humans to animals (the latter is sometimes called reverse zoonosis or anthroponosis). In a study of 1415 pathogens known to affect humans, 61% were zoonotic. The emergence of a pathogen into a new host species is called disease invasion.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Rabid_dog.jpg/230px-Rabid_dog.jpg
